00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,530
[SIGHS]

243
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,160
And look at the way...

244
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,690
...they've slathered
those pigs with cosmetics.

245
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:03,820
So sad, yet so sexy, yet so delicious.
Mm.

246
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:07,230
Dad, today was so great.

247
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:11,330
The animal rights protest, a visit to
the Museum of Sadness and Oppression.

248
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,650
Well, we should get along.

249
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:17,100
I mean, after all, I am your father.

250
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:20,670
How'd you think of such perfect things
for us to do? Did Mom help you?

251
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,700
Mom? Don't you think
I could read the report by myself?

252
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,960
- What report?
- The... Uh...

253
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:30,680
Well, uh, report is a daddy word
that means "loves his daughter."

254
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:34,570
You read the "loves his daughter"
by yourself?

255
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,160
That's right, honey.

256
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,080
You did it.
Lisa thinks I'm the greatest.

257
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,450
I might even put you to work
on Bart and Maggie.

258
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,430
Go super dad on all their asses.

259
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,120
I believe there's still the matter
of my expenses.

260
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,890
Oh, yes.
Well, let's take a look and see...

261
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,010
A thousand dollars?

262
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,180
- How did you spend a thousand dollars?
- It's itemized.

263
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:59,230
A $40 steak?

264
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,960
But if I'd eaten the whole thing,
it would've been free.

265
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,230
You've been living
like a king on my dollar.

266
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:06,850
Super-unleaded gas. Silver bullets?

267
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:09,960
I was working under the theory
that your daughter was a werewolf.

268
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,050
- Didn't pan out.
- I can't believe a man who agreed...

269
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:16,060
...to follow my daughter around
for money...

270
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,390
...would turn out to be a dirtbag.

271
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,050
You better pay up, Simpson.

272
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:22,790
[WHIMPERING]

273
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,970
[GRUNTS]

274
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,890
You'll regret the day
you crossed Dexter Colt.

275
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,880
You'll regret the day you went
to the expensive coffee place.

276
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,890
<i>[THE WINSTONS'</i>
<i>"COLOR HIM FATHER" PLAYING]</i>

277
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,750
<i>I think I'll color him love</i>

278
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,460
<i>Color him love</i>

279
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:41,230
Breaking news at the Screaming Monkey
Research Labs...

280
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:44,110
...where test animals have been freed
by unknown activists.

281
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,110
Chief Wiggum, uh,
do you have a statement?

282
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:49,570
Uh, yes. Yes, I do, Kent.
This is a horrible crime.

283
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,570
One that... Ha, ha.

284
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,400
Cut it out, Lou. I...

285
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,960
He's making funny faces.

286
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,740
Sorry, chief. One of these monkeys
has the same name as my ex-wife.

287
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,170
[LAUGHS]

288
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,610
Chief, do you have any suspects
at this time?

289
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,040
Well, we do have
several promising clues.

290
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,870
Uh, let's see.
There's a Malibu Stacy scrunchie...

291
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,520
...a saxophone reed...

292
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:13,250
...and a book report on <i>The
Secret Garden </i>by Lisa Simpson.

293
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,080
What does this tell you?

294
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:18,140
Well, apparently,
there's a secret garden in all of us.

295
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,540
And that Lisa Simpson is guilty.

296
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,160
[HOMER, LISA AND MARGE GASP]

297
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:23,360
I was framed.

298
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:25,540
- You believe me, don't you, Dad?
- Of course I do.

299
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,700
It's all my fault for refusing to pay...

300
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:35,050
Pay attention to you, my sweet little
father-loving pile of forgiveness.

301
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:36,760
Yes.

302
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,550
[KNOCKING]

303
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,370
Can Lisa come out
with her hands up?

304
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:47,770
Chief Wiggum, my daughter is innocent
until proven guilty.

305
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,800
[TIRES SCREECH]

306
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,110
Would an innocent person flee?

307
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,400
No, really. Tell me.
I honestly don't know.

308
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,630
- Chief, no.
- Even I knew that.

309
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,680
Yeah, yeah, I'm not... I'm not good.

310
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,640
[SIRENS WAILING]

311
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,810
Ha, ha. They're trapped.

312
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,660
Oh, damn it.

313
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:20,880
[MARGE SIGHS]

314
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,830
I can't stop worrying
about Homer and Lisa.

315
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,420
Oh, Mom.
This'll take your mind off them. Unh!

316
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:31,530
Oh, thank you, sweetie.

317
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,020
[MARGE HUMS]

318
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,480
[BREAKS]

319
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,650
BROCKMAN [ON RADIO]: <i>Police are</i>
<i>looking for a bald man in blue pants...</i>

320
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,060
<i>...and a fair-haired girl</i>
<i>in a red lampshade.</i>

321
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,990
Blackening our hair
was a great idea, Dad.

322
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,480
I look just like a Powerpuff Girl.

323
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:48,380
I look just like Elvis.

324
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,160
[GROANS]

325
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,800
- Names, please?
- Lady Penelope Ariel Ponyweather.

326
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,190
Uh, Rock Strongo.

327
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:00,580
Your real name?

328
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,830
- Uh, Lance Uppercut.
- Thank you.

329
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,740
Sign here, Mr. Uppercut.

330
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:08,120
Let me just put on my glasses.

331
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,780
You're charging how much for a room?

332
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:18,160
[PHONE RINGS]

333
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,320
Hello?

334
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:22,030
HOMER [ON PHONE]:
<i>Hello. This is a phone survey.</i>

335
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,420
If the election were held today...

336
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:27,480
...would you vote for A,
the cops are there...

337
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:30,390
...or B, you're free to talk.

338
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,410
Uh, A. And I'd like to add...

339
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:38,000
...that proposition "Hug Lisa For Me"
has my full support.

340
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:41,600
Oh, Marge. You're not getting it.
It's me, Homer Simpson.

341
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,040
[CHUCKLES]

342
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,830
- We got a location, chief.
- Good work, Lou.

343
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:48,220
We'll leave right after dinner.

344
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:51,400
Lisa, this is from your mom.

345
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,530
Aw. Life on the lam is really hard.

346
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,510
But at least it's with you, Dad.

347
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:58,780
I feel terrible
for putting you through this...

348
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,630
...after what a wonderful father
you've been.

349
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,040
Oh. Lisa, I can't lie to you any longer.

350
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:06,890
This is all my fault.

351
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:09,000
I'm the worst dad in the world.

352
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,490
What? Why?

353
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:13,580
The man who framed you
is a crooked detective who I hired.

354
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,390
Why did you do that?

355
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,430
To find out everything about you
so I'd seem like a good father.

356
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,300
How could you?

357
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:23,560
Well, all the childless drunks at Moe's
thought it was a great idea.

358
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:26,370
Let's just get some sleep.

359
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:37,200
All right, Simpsons, the jig is up.
We know you're in there.

360
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,830
HOMER:
Okay. I'm coming right out the door.

361
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:42,710
Damn it. These windows are so hard
to squeeze through.

362
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,710
[HOMER GRUNTS]

363
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:54,760
Cheer up, honey. We're living an
all-natural existence, the kind you like.

364
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,560
Ooh, a trash can.

365
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,290
We'll find breakfast in here.

366
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,290
I don't wanna eat from the trash.

367
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,880
Oh, a banana.

368
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:06,660
What the...? It's full of cigarette butts.

369
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:08,180
So is this one.

370
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,910
They must've come from over there.

371
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,310
Those are the test animals.

372
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,750
The detective must've sold them
to the circus.

373
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,400
We'll just tell the police...

374
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:24,830
...and then I'm back
to being plain old Rock Strongo.

375
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,490
COLT:
You're not telling nobody nothing.

376
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:31,100
Make one move and you'll get a belly
full of the Flying Giuseppe.

377
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,150
How you doing?

378
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:36,460
Dexter Colt,
the man who framed my daughter.

379
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,260
- You should've paid the expenses.
- In retrospect, yes.

380
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,190
[GASPS]

381
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:51,990
[HOMER GRUNTS]

382
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:54,070
Ooh. I think that fixed my back.

383
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,390
[CRACKING]

384
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:56,730
Oh, no, no. It's much worse.

385
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,050
I'll just hide here.

386
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,560
[YELPS]

387
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,870
[YELPS]

388
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,400
[WHIMPERING]

389
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:12,200
[LAUGHS]

390
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:13,390
Now what are you gonna do?

391
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:16,000
You can't shoot all of us. Damn it.

392
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:20,570
You know, Simpson, from the moment
you walked into my office...

393
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,440
...I had a feeling I'd kill you
in a hall of mirrors.

394
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,220
Dad? Are you in here?

395
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:28,340
- How did she find us?
- Oh, Lisa has excellent hearing.

396
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:31,480
Once when she was 3,
I was quietly sobbing in the closet...

397
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:32,910
...and she found me.

398
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,450
Oh, Dad, you do remember
something about me.

399
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,980
Perhaps you also remember
this laser Bart gave me earlier.

400
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:41,240
[GRUNTS]

401
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,390
I can't see.

402
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:45,720
How ironic.

403
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:50,190
Now, he's blind after a life
of enjoying being able to see.

404
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:54,950
Well, it wasn't easy, honey.

405
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,790
But I'm glad you love me again.

406
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:59,370
Yeah. But what's gonna happen
to the animals?

407
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:02,440
Don't worry, honey.
They released them all into the wild.

408
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,720
[MONKEYS GIBBERING
AND PIGS GRUNTING]

409
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,800
Cletus, if I find pig lipstick
on your collar again...

410
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,360
...I'm not gonna let you sleep
in the sty no more.

411
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:12,000
Duly noted.

412
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,320
BART:
Hey, Dad. Will you read me a story?

413
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,020
HOMER:
Why certainly, son.

414
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,260
Just hand me that book you got there.

415
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,720
COMPUTER VOICE:
<i>Unauthorized user. Access denied.</i>

416
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,600
[BOOK BUZZING
AND HOMER SCREAMING]

417
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,790
[BART LAUGHING]

418
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:57,860
WOMAN:
Shh.

419
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:03,600
[English - US -SDH]